                <p>
                    With a waterproof polymer housing, stainless fittings, supercharged amplifier and a large load cell this unit is ready for the greenhouse.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Advanced signal processing and design makes this unit compatible with the common greenhouse technique of "flow-through". 
                    Because irrigation water has some salts in it, it is common to rinse the potting media regularly. That means irrigating 
                    so much that a fraction of the irrigation water runs out of the bottom of the pot.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The convoluted top plate of this Wely slows water flow during a flow-through event. With advanced signal processing
                    this technique allows the device to provide accurate data of how much water was delivered, even though not all water is absorbed by the growing media.
                    The data can then be used to calibrate the irrigation system.
                </p>
            </section>
